#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Number of Matrix Paths (Recursion)

Question:
Top-left se bottom-right tak jaana hai matrix mein,
sirf 2 moves allowed hain:
1. Right
2. Down

Hume total number of paths count karne hain.

--------------------------------------------------
Main Idea
--------------------------------------------------
Har cell par khade ho kar humare paas 2 choices hoti hain:
1. Right jao
2. Down jao

To total paths = paths from right + paths from down

Isliye recurrence relation:
numberOfPaths(m, n) = numberOfPaths(m-1, n) + numberOfPaths(m, n-1)

--------------------------------------------------
Base Case
--------------------------------------------------
Agar hum last row ya last column par pahunch gaye,
to waha se sirf ek hi straight path bachta hai.

Isliye:
if(m == 1 || n == 1) return 1;

Matlab:
1 row bachi -> sirf right ja sakte ho
1 column bacha -> sirf down ja sakte ho

--------------------------------------------------
Recursive Breakdown
--------------------------------------------------
numberOfPaths(m-1, n) -> down move
numberOfPaths(m, n-1) -> right move

Dono paths ko add kar denge.

--------------------------------------------------
Example
--------------------------------------------------
M = 2, N = 2

Paths:
Right -> Down
Down -> Right

Total = 2

Formula:
f(2,2) = f(1,2) + f(2,1)
       = 1 + 1
       = 2

--------------------------------------------------
Recursion Tree (2 x 3)
--------------------------------------------------
f(2,3)
= f(1,3) + f(2,2)
= 1 + (f(1,2) + f(2,1))
= 1 + (1 + 1)
= 3

--------------------------------------------------
Time Complexity
--------------------------------------------------
Har call 2 aur calls bana rahi hai:
Time ≈ O(2^(m+n))

--------------------------------------------------
Space Complexity
--------------------------------------------------
Recursion stack:
O(m+n)

--------------------------------------------------
One line intuition
--------------------------------------------------
Har cell se ya to right ja sakte ho ya down,
isliye total paths = right ke paths + down ke paths.

Quick Revision – Matrix Paths

f(m, n) = f(m-1, n) + f(m, n-1)

Base case:
m == 1 || n == 1 -> 1

Moves allowed:
Right or Down

Time: Exponential
Space: O(m+n)

#Code:

public class Solution {

    public static int numberOfPaths(int m, int n) {

        //You can code here
        //Base case
        if(n==1 || m==1){
          return 1;
        }
        return numberOfPaths(m-1,n) + numberOfPaths(m, n-1);
      

    }
}
